<TITLE> Ronaldinho to miss Almeria game with injury </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, March 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Ronaldinho was added to Barcelona's lengthy injury list ahead of the trip to Almeria in the Primera Liga on Sunday. The Brazil forward has a groin strain and was left out of the squad along with Lionel Messi, Giovani dos Santos, Deco, Yaya Toure and Rafael Marquez. Fullback Gianluca Zambrotta is suspended so coach Frank Rijkaard included three B team players for the trip south. Leaders Real Madrid, who have an eight-point advantage over second-placed Barca, were at Deportivo Coruna on Saturday
